# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# A comprehensive .gitignore for a monorepo:
# - Frontend: React (Vite) + TypeScript
# - Backend:  ASP.NET Core 8
# - Infra:    AWS CDK (C#)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. General: IDE, OS, and Secret Files
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# OS-generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE - Visual Studio Code
.vscode/*
*.code-workspace

# IDE - Visual Studio / JetBrains Rider
**/.vs/
**/.idea/
**/*.user
**/*.suo

# Local secret files
# Use `secrets.json` (via .NET User Secrets) or `.env.local` for local development
# NEVER commit sensitive data.
*.local
secrets.json
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env

# Log files
*.log
*.logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Frontend: Node.js / React / Vite
# (Matches files in `src/frontend/`)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# Dependencies
**/node_modules/

# Build output (Vite's default is `dist`)
**/dist/

# Test output and cache
**/coverage/
.nyc_output/
.vitest-cache/

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Backend & Infrastructure: .NET / C#
# (Matches files in `src/backend/` and `src/infrastructure/`)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build output
**/[Bb]in/
**/[Oo]bj/

# Publish output
**/publish/

# User-specific files
**/*.userprefs
**/*.resharper
**/*.[Rr]e[Ss]harper

# NuGet packages folder
**/packages/
*.nupkg

# .NET temporary files
*.Generated.cs
*.cache

# Entity Framework migration files
# (It's a best practice to commit these, so they are NOT ignored)

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. AWS CDK
# (Matches files in `src/infrastructure/`)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

# AWS CDK synthesized artifacts (CloudFormation templates, assets)
**/cdk.out/

# AWS CDK context cache (stores VPCs, AZs, etc. from your account)
# Ignoring this ensures a clean, non-account-specific build
**/cdk.context.json

# AWS CDK crash reports
**/cdk-crash-report-*.json